CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 28, 1953, pg. 17 reads: "New Yorker...Mrs. Bertha J. Diggs, secretary of labor for the State of New York, came to represent Governor Thomas E. Dewey."
TitMainTitle: Bertha J. Diggs, speaking at microphone on stage with men and women seated behind her including Jessie Vann, Toki Schalk Johnson, Bill Nunn Sr., and Alma Illery, in Penn Sheraton ballroom with sunburst patterned curtains for Jessie Vann's birthday party
